eived, developed or reduced to practice or learned by me alone or jointly with others at any time during the term of my employment with the Company which: \r\n\r\n(a) relate to the actual or anticipated business, work, research or investigations of the Company or any of its affiliates, or \r\n\r\n(b) result from or are suggested by any work done for the Company or any of its affiliates: or \r\n\r\n(c) are conceived or made on the time of, or with the use of the facilities or materials of, the Company or any of its affiliates ( collectively referred to as "Company Inventions") \r\n\r\n3. Waiver of Moral Rights. The Employee irrevocably waives any and all moral rights that the Employee may have to all Company Inventions, which moral rights are acknowledged to include the right to the integrity of the Company Inventions, the right to restrain or claim damages for any distortion, mutilation or other modification of any part of the Company Inventions, the right to be associated with the Company Inventions as an author by name or under an assumed name, the right to remain anonymous when any translation of the Company Inventions is produced, performed or published, and the right to restrain use or reproduction of the Company Invention in any contest and in connection with any product or service. \r\n\r\n4. Records. During the period of my employment and thereafter, Employee will promptly disclose to the Company fully and in writing all Company Inventions authored, made, conceived or reduced to practice by me, either alone or jointly with others. At the request of the Company, Employee further agrees to keep and maintain adequate and current records (in the form of notes, sketches, drawings and in any other form that may be required by the Company) of all information \r\n\r\n(a) developed by me regarding plans for research, development, new products, marketing and selling, business plans, budgets and unpublished financial statements, licenses, prices and costs, suppliers and customers; and \r\n\r\n(b) all Company Inventions authored, made, conceived or reduced to practice by me during the period of my employment at the Company, which records shall be available to and remain the sole property of the Company at all times. \r\n\r\n5. Enforcement of Proprietary Rights. Employee will assist the Company, at the Company\'s expense, in every proper way to obtain, and from time to time enforce, Proprietary Rights relating to Company Inventions in any and all countries. Employee will execute, verify and deliver such documents and perform such other acts (including appearances as a witness) as the Company may reasonably request in connection with applying for, obtaining, perfecting, evidencing, sustaining and enforcing such Proprietary Rights and the assignment thereof. In addition, Employee will execute, verify and deliver specific assignments of Company Inventions (and all Proprietary Rights with respect thereto) to the Company or its nominee. Employee\'s obligations under this Section shall continue beyond the termination of my employment. \r\n\r\n\r\nIf the Company is unable for any reason, after reasonable effort, to secure my signature on any document needed in connection with the actions specified in the preceding paragraph, Employee hereby irrevocably designates and appoints the Company and its duly authorized officers and agents as my agent and attorney in fact, which appointment is coupled with an interest, to act for and on my behalf to execute, verify and file any such documents and to do all other lawfully permitted acts to further the purposes of the preceding paragraph with the same legal force and effect as if executed by me. \r\n\r\n6. Nondisclosure. At all times during Employee\'s employment by the Company and thereafter, Employee will hold in strictest confidence and will not disclose, use, lecture upon or publish any of the Proprietary Information (defined below) of the Company or any of its affiliates, except as such disclosure, use or publication may be required in connection with my work for the Company, [or unless an officer of the Company expressly authorizes such in writing]. Employee will obtain the Company\'s written approval before publishing or submitting for publication any material (written, verbal, or otherwise) that relates to my work at the Company and/or incorporates any Proprietary Information. Employee hereby assigns, and shall assign, to the Company or its nominee any rights Employee may have or acquire in such Proprietary Information and recognize that all Proprietary Information shall be the sole property of the Company and its assigns. \r\n\r\nThe term "Proprietary Information" means any and all confidential and/or proprietary knowledge, data or information of the Company, its successors or assigns, or any of their respective affiliates. By way of illustration but not limitation, "Proprietary Information" includes \r\n\r\n(a) any Inventions; and \r\n\r\n(b) information regarding plans for research, development, new products, marketing and selling, business plans, budgets and unpublished financial statements, licenses, prices and costs, suppliers and customers; and \r\n\r\n(c) information regarding the skills and compensation of other employees of the Company or any of its affiliates. Notwithstanding the foregoing, it is understood that, at all such times, Employee is free to use information which is or becomes generally known to the public other than through a breach of this Agreement. \r\n\r\n\r\n7. Third Party Information. Employee understands, in addition, that the Company has received and in the future will receive information from third parties ("Third Party Information") subject to a duty on the Company\'s part to maintain the confidentiality of such information and to use it only for certain limited purposes. During the term of my employment and thereafter, Employee will hold Third Party Information in the strictest confidence and will not disclose to anyone (other than Company personnel who need to know such information in connection with their work for the Company) or use, except in connection with my work for the Company and in compliance with the Company\'s obligations to third parties regarding confidentiality and use, Third Party Information [unless expressly authorized by an officer of the Company in writing]. \r\n\r\n\r\n8 No Improper Use of Information of Prior Employers and Others. During Employee\'s employment by the Company, Employee will not improperly use or disclose any confidential information, trade secrets, Proprietary Rights, or other information, if any, of any former employer or any other person to whom Employee has an obligation of confidentiality, and Employee will not bring onto the premises of the Company any unpublished documents or any property belonging to any former employer or any other person to whom Employee has an obligation of confidentiality unless consented to in writing by that former employer or person. \r\n\r\n\r\n9 No Conflicting Obligation. Employee represents that the performance of my duties of employment does not and will not breach any agreement which may still be in effect: \r\n\r\n(a) to keep in confidence information acquired by me in confidence or in trust prior to my employment by the Company; \r\n\r\nor (b) and/or (b) which would otherwise have a bearing on my employment with the Company. Employee has not entered into, and Employee agrees that Employee will not enter into, any agreement either written or oral in conflict with the provisions of this Agreement. \r\n\r\n\r\n10. Return of Materials. When Employee leaves the employ of the Company, Employee will deliver to the Company any and all drawings, notes, memoranda, specifications, devices, formulas, and documents, together with all copies thereof, and any other material containing or disclosing any Company Inventions, Third Party Information or Proprietary Information of the Company (including, without limitation, any material stored in electronic form on computer hard drives or on portable storage media). If any computer hard drives or portable storage media that are not required to be returned to the Company store such material, then Employee will purge the material after printing copies thereof and providing them to the Company. \r\n\r\n11. Legal and Equitable Remedies. Employee understands and agrees that the Company will suffer irreparable injury if Employee breaches any of the provisions of this Agreement and that monetary damages will not provide an adequate remedy to the Company. Accordingly, if Employee commits a breach, or threaten to commit a breach, of any of the provisions of this Agreement, the Company shall have the right to enforce this Agreement and any of its provisions by injunction, specific performance or other equitable relief, without the posting of bond or other security or proof of actual damages and without prejudice to any other rights and remedies that the Company may have for a breach of this Agreement. \r\n\r\n\r\n12. Notification of New Employer. In the event that Employee leaves the employ of the Company, Employee hereby consents to the notification of my new employer of my rights and obligations under this Agreement. \r\n\r\n13. General Provisions. \r\n\r\n(a) Notices. Any notices required or permitted hereunder shall be given to me at my address as last shown on the records of the Company. Such notice shall be deemed given upon personal delivery to the address specified or if sent by certified or registered mail, three (3) days after the date of mailing. \r\n\r\n(b) Governing Law. This Agreement will be governed by and construed according to the laws of the Province or State in which Employee performs my principal duties of employment. Employee hereby submits to the jurisdiction of the Courts located in such Province or State for the purposes of this Agreement. \r\n\r\n(c) Severability. If any of the provisions contained in this Agreement are 